Release & DevOps Specialist 
Location: Bedfordview (Hybrid possible) 
Employment Type: Full-Time, Permanent 
Industry: Insurance | IT Development | DevOps & Release Engineering 
WatersEdge Solutions is partnering with a leading long-term insurance provider to recruit a 
Release & DevOps Specialist. This critical role is focused on ensuring smooth, consistent, and 
high-quality software releases. You'll serve as a key link between development, QA, and 
operations—driving the delivery of scalable, production-grade software systems in a 
collaborative environment. 
About the Role 
You will take ownership of the release calendar, CI/CD automation, and environment 
stability—empowering dev teams to focus on building features while ensuring the business 
receives robust, production-ready software. Your efforts will directly enhance deployment quality, 
system observability, and business confidence in release cycles. 
Key Responsibilities 
● Manage and own the software release calendar and coordination 
● Plan, communicate, and document release processes across environments 
● Build and maintain CI/CD pipelines using Azure DevOps 
● Automate deployment processes across development, staging, and production 
● Maintain parity between staging and production environments 
● Implement rollback strategies and recovery processes 
● Collaborate with IT and QA to ensure environments are secure and production-like 
● Troubleshoot and resolve staging/production issues 
● Provide visibility via dashboards and release readiness metrics 
What You’ll Bring 
● Strong experience with CI/CD pipelines in Azure DevOps 
● Proficiency in automated deployments for .NET, Blazor, and SQL Server 
● Expert knowledge of Git branching strategies 
● Solid troubleshooting skills across code, configuration, and environments 
● Familiarity with release/change management in enterprise settings 
● High attention to detail and structured thinking 
● Ownership mindset and collaborative working style 
Nice to Have 
● Experience with observability tools (e.g., Seq) 
● Understanding of security protocols for deployment (secrets, IAM, access policies) 
● Scripting knowledge (PowerShell, Bash, or Python) 
● Containerisation and infrastructure automation experience 
What’s On Offer 
● High-impact DevOps role in a stable and long-standing company 
● Hybrid working model (Bedfordview-based) 
● Opportunity to shape release processes and improve deployment frequency 
● Direct collaboration with development, QA, and IT 
● Exposure to modern DevOps tools and enterprise standards 
Company Culture 
The client cultivates a mission-driven, member-centred culture rooted in empathy, reliability, and 
service excellence. Their teams operate with compassion at the core -ensuring clients feel 
heard, supported, and respected through every personal interaction. With a strong emphasis on 
operational integrity, efficiency, and clear communication, they aim to minimise friction during 
life’s most challenging moments. Internally, they uphold a culture of accountability, fairness, and 
trust, fostering a workplace where every team member is empowered to do meaningful work in 
service of others.
